article.headline: CS Northridge 70, Cal St.-Fullerton 68
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Josh Greene scored 19 points and hit the clinching 3-pointer as Cal State Northridge rallied from a 14-point second-half deficit to edge Cal State Fullerton 70-68 Thursday night. Greene made six baskets, all from 3-point range, as the Matadors (10-14, 7-4 Big West) won for the sixth time in eight games. After the Gauchos' Michael Lizarraga tied it at 66 with 1:20 left, Perry Webster's two free throws put the Titans back ahead. But Greene nailed a 3-pointer with 24 seconds left for a 69-68 lead, and Lizarraga tacked on a free throw. Lenny Daniel had a double-double of 11 points and 11 rebounds for Cal State Northridge, and Rashaun McLemore and Lizarraga scored 10 apiece. Andre Hardy led the Titans (9-16, 5-7) with 19 points and 12 rebounds. Jer'Vaughn Johnson and Orlando Brown scored 16 each. Cal State Fullerton led 50-36 with 13:20 left before Northridge stormed back.
